This template creates an [[WP:UBLIST|unbulleted list]] for [[WP:CITEBUNDLE|bundled citations]]. It works with [[Help:Shortened footnotes|shortened footnotes]], [[Wikipedia:Citation templates|full citations]], and general notes. The standard {{t|unbulleted list}} template will disrupt white space within references. It causes an unnecessary line break before the first list item. See below for comparisons:

Bundled citation with <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>{{unbulleted list citebundle}}</syntaxhighlight>: <ref>
{{Unbulleted list citebundle|For the sun's size, see {{cite book|last=Miller|first=Edward|title=The Sun|publisher=Academic Press|year=2005|page=1|ref=none}}
|For the moon's size, see {{cite journal|last=Brown|first=Rebecca|title=Size of the Moon|journal=Scientific American|volume=51|issue=78|date=2007|page=46|ref=none}}
|For the sun's heat, see {{cite book|author1-mask={{translit|ja|italic=no|Hepburn|Yamada, Hanako}} [{{lang|ja|山田花子}}]|last=山田|first=花子|script-title=ja:太陽の熱|title={{translit|ja|Hepburn|Taiyō no netsu}}|trans-title=The Sun's Heat|publisher={{translit|ja|Hepburn|Gakujutsu shuppansha}} ({{lang|ja|学術出版社}}) [Academic Press]|year=2005|page=2|ref=none}}}}</ref>
{{reflist}}

Versus incorrect rendering with <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>{{unbulleted list}}</syntaxhighlight>:<ref>
{{Unbulleted list|For the sun's size, see {{cite book|last=Miller|first=Edward|title=The Sun|publisher=Academic Press|year=2005|page=1|ref=none}}
|For the moon's size, see {{cite journal|last=Brown|first=Rebecca|title=Size of the Moon|journal=Scientific American|volume=51|issue=78|date=2007|page=46|ref=none}}
|For the sun's heat, see {{cite book|author1-mask={{translit|ja|italic=no|Hepburn|Yamada, Hanako}} [{{lang|ja|山田花子}}]|last=山田|first=花子|script-title=ja:太陽の熱|title={{translit|ja|Hepburn|Taiyō no netsu}}|trans-title=The Sun's Heat|publisher={{translit|ja|Hepburn|Gakujutsu shuppansha}} ({{lang|ja|学術出版社}}) [Academic Press]|year=2005|page=2|ref=none}}}}</ref>
{{reflist}}

==Usage==
If any of the [[H:T#Hints and workarounds|unnamed parameters]] contain an equal sign (=) in their text (not in their use of parameters in other templates), the parameter must be named in the usual way, {{tlf|Unbulleted list citebundle|2=1=}}. E.g.
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>{{Unbulleted list citebundle|[https://www.naxos.com/CatalogueDetail/?id=SWR19026CD "''Festliche Arien – Fritz Wunderlich''"], [[Naxos Records]] SWR19026CD}}</syntaxhighlight> will produce no output. But <code><nowiki>{{Unbulleted list citebundle|</nowiki>{{highlight|1=1=}}<nowiki>[https://www.naxos.com/CatalogueDetail/?id=SWR19026CD "''Festliche Arien – Fritz Wunderlich''"], [[Naxos Records]] SWR19026CD}}</nowiki></code> works as expected:
{{Unbulleted list citebundle|1=[https://www.naxos.com/CatalogueDetail/?id=SWR19026CD "''Festliche Arien – Fritz Wunderlich''"], [[Naxos Records]] SWR19026CD}}
===With "cite" templates===
The wiki text for the initial example above uses {{cite xxx}} templates for the footnotes:

{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>Body text.<ref>
{{Unbulleted list citebundle | For the sun's size, see {{cite book | last=Miller | first=Edward | title=The Sun | publisher=Academic Press | year=2005 | page=1 | ref=none}}
 | For the moon's size, see {{cite journal | last=Brown | first=Rebecca | title=Size of the Moon | journal=Scientific American | volume=51 | issue=78 | year=2007 | page=46 | ref=none}}
 | For the sun's heat, see {{cite book | author1-mask={{translit | ja | italic=no | Hepburn | Yamada, Hanako}} [{{lang | ja | 山田花子}}] | last=山田 | first=花子 | script-title=ja:太陽の熱 | title={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Taiyō no netsu}} | trans-title=The Sun's Heat | publisher={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Gakujutsu shuppansha}} ({{lang | ja | 学術出版社}}) [Academic Press] | year=2005 | page=2 | ref=none}} }}</ref>
{{reflist}}
</syntaxhighlight >|Body text.<ref>
{{Unbulleted list citebundle | For the sun's size, see {{cite book | last=Miller | first=Edward | title=The Sun | publisher=Academic Press | year=2005 | page=1 | ref=none}}
 | For the moon's size, see {{cite journal | last=Brown | first=Rebecca | title=Size of the Moon | journal=Scientific American | volume=51 | issue=78 | year=2007 | page=46 | ref=none}}
 | For the sun's heat, see {{cite book | author1-mask={{translit | ja | italic=no | Hepburn | Yamada, Hanako}} [{{lang | ja | 山田花子}}] | last=山田 | first=花子 | script-title=ja:太陽の熱 | title={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Taiyō no netsu}} | trans-title=The Sun's Heat | publisher={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Gakujutsu shuppansha}} ({{lang | ja | 学術出版社}}) [Academic Press] | year=2005 | page=2 | ref=none}} }}</ref>
{{reflist}}
}}
===Multiref and shortened footnotes===

The template can also be called as {{t|multiref}} for easier typing. The example below uses [[Help:Shortened footnotes|shortened footnotes]].

{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>
Text.<ref>{{multiref|Smith, p. 2|Jones, p. 105|Singh, p. 93|Lee ''et al.'', p. 22|Smith & Jones, p. 591}}</ref>{{reflist}}</syntaxhighlight >|Text.<ref>{{multiref|Smith, p. 2|Jones, p. 105|Singh, p. 93|Lee ''et al.'', p. 22|Smith & Jones, p. 591}}</ref>{{reflist}}}}
===With "harv" templates===

Harvard-style templates create short citations that link to full citations. This template can be used to bundle short citations created by {{t|harvnb}}, {{t|harvtxt}}, and others.

{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>Text.<ref> {{Unbulleted list citebundle| {{harvnb|山田|2005|p=2}} | {{harvnb|Brown|2007|p=105}} | {{harvnb|Miller|2005|p=93}} }}</ref>{{reflist}}
</syntaxhighlight >

|Text.<ref> {{Unbulleted list citebundle| {{harvnb|山田|2005|p=2}} | {{harvnb|Brown|2007|p=105}} | {{harvnb|Miller|2005|p=93}} }}</ref>{{reflist}}
}}

Example references for the linked footnotes above:

* {{cite book | author1-mask={{translit | ja | italic=no | Hepburn | Yamada, Hanako}} [{{lang | ja | 山田花子}}] | last=山田 | first=花子 | script-title=ja:太陽の熱 | title={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Taiyō no netsu}} | trans-title=The Sun's Heat | publisher={{translit | ja | Hepburn | Gakujutsu shuppansha}} ({{lang | ja | 学術出版社}}) [Academic Press] | year=2005}}
* {{cite journal | last=Brown | first=Rebecca | title=Size of the Moon | journal=Scientific American | volume=51 | issue=78 | year=2007}}
* {{cite book | last=Miller | first=Edward | title=The Sun | publisher=Academic Press | year=2005}}
===One source citing another===

This is where the editor cannot, or has not, accessed the source verifying the claim, but instead has cited a second source providing a quote from the first source. Using this template makes it clear that there are two relevant items in the bibliography.

{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>Text.<ref>{{multiref|Smith, p. 2 citing|Jones, p. 105}}</ref>{{reflist}}
</syntaxhighlight >|Text.<ref>{{multiref|Smith, p. 2 citing|Jones, p. 105}}</ref>{{reflist}}}}
===Explanatory notes===

One possible reason for adding an explanatory note is to make it clear that the citation leads to an example of the claimed fact, not to verification of the claim itself which may be in a later cite.

{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>There are many breeds of cat found in Venezuela,<ref>{{multiref|For example,|Moggie, p. 2|Tom, p. 95}}</ref> particular in the cities.<ref>Smith, p. 32</ref>{{reflist}}
</syntaxhighlight >|There are many breeds of cat found in Venezuela,<ref>{{multiref|For example,|Moggie, p. 2|Tom, p. 95}}</ref> particular in the cities.<ref>Smith, p. 32</ref>{{reflist}}}}
Explanatory note with a single citation:
{{Markup|<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>There are many breeds of cat found in Venezuela,<ref>{{multiref|One example,|Moggie, p. 2}}</ref> particular in the cities.<ref>Smith, p. 32</ref>{{reflist}}
</syntaxhighlight >|There are many breeds of cat found in Venezuela,<ref>{{multiref|One example,|Moggie, p. 2}}</ref> particular in the cities.<ref>Smith, p. 32</ref>{{reflist}}}}

===Known problems===
The template works, in part, by suppressing line breaks in the specified references.  This works poorly if the page is sufficiently short that the references collide with an infobox or picture.  In those cases, use one of the {{template|clear}} variants or {{template|multiref2}}.  

